target_markets.market_description: Entrepreneurs wanting to start AI automation agencies, split between technical and non-technical founders
pain_points: lack of technical expertise for non-technical founders
target_markets.market_size_indicators: 100,000 members in free school community, significant portion are AI developers looking for work

problems_validated.problem: Non-technical founders struggling to start AI automation agencies without development skills
problems_validated.current_solutions: Hiring freelance developers, learning to code
problems_validated.market_gap: Lack of structured guidance on team building and scaling phases

problems_validated.problem: Agency owners not knowing what focus areas and team requirements are needed at each revenue stage
problems_validated.current_solutions: Trial and error, generic business advice
problems_validated.market_gap: No phase-specific roadmap for AI automation agencies

products_tools.name: Calendly
products_tools.metrics: part of startup phase tech stack

business_strategies.strategy: Revenue share model with freelance developers (20-30% split)
business_strategies.implementation: Partner with AI developers from community, share revenue based on project delivery
business_strategies.expected_results: Allows non-technical founders to deliver projects without upfront developer costs
business_strategies.case_study: At $5K monthly revenue with 20% revenue share, costs are $1K per month to developer

business_strategies.strategy: Warm outreach through existing network for first clients
business_strategies.implementation: Start with free clients through warm connections, graduate to paid clients
business_strategies.case_study: Focus on warm outreach method for 0-5K phase

business_strategies.strategy: Phase-based scaling with specific team requirements per revenue stage
business_strategies.implementation: Different team structure and focus areas for each revenue milestone (0-5K, 5-10K, etc.)
business_strategies.expected_results: Systematic scaling from 0 to $100K monthly revenue
business_strategies.case_study: 5 distinct phases each with specific team and tech stack requirements

problems_solutions.problem: Non-technical founders can't deliver AI automation projects
problems_solutions.solution: Partner with freelance AI developers on revenue share basis
steps: Find AI developers looking for work

problems_solutions.problem: Scaling warm outreach manually becomes overwhelming
problems_solutions.solution: Hire virtual assistant for admin support and systematic outreach
steps: Hire VA in early growth phase (5-10K revenue)

startup_ideas.idea: AI automation agency targeting general custom AI development
startup_ideas.target_market: Businesses needing custom AI solutions and automation
startup_ideas.problem_solved: Companies lack internal AI development capabilities
startup_ideas.business_model: Custom AI development projects, revenue share with developers
startup_ideas.validation: Start with warm network, free initial projects, graduate to paid
startup_ideas.investment_needed: Low initial investment, mainly revenue share costs

mistakes_to_avoid.mistake: Taking on large $15,000 projects too early or trying to build productized offerings immediately
mistakes_to_avoid.consequences: Overwhelm, lack of experience to deliver, potential failure
mistakes_to_avoid.prevention: Start small with baby steps, gradually build confidence and experience
mistakes_to_avoid.example: Focus on small projects in startup phase rather than complex offerings

mistakes_to_avoid.mistake: Trying to do everything manually without systems as you scale
mistakes_to_avoid.consequences: Bottlenecks in growth, inability to handle increased lead volume
mistakes_to_avoid.prevention: Hire VA early in growth phase to build systems and scale outreach
mistakes_to_avoid.example: Move from manual messaging to systematic tracking and follow-ups

growth_tactics.tactic: Leverage free school community with 100K members for developer recruitment
growth_tactics.cost_estimate: Free to join, revenue share costs only
growth_tactics.results_expected: Access to pool of AI developers looking for work
Gradual confidence building and client acquisition

metrics_kpis.optimization_tip: Focus on specific team and strategy requirements per phase

metrics_kpis.tracking_method: Track developer costs vs total revenue
metrics_kpis.optimization_tip: Adjust percentage based on developer skill and project complexity

trends_signals.trend: High demand for AI developers in automation agency space
trends_signals.opportunity: Large pool of available AI developers seeking work opportunities

trends_signals.trend: Non-technical entrepreneurs entering AI automation space
trends_signals.opportunity: Revenue share model enables non-technical founders to enter market
